<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9316BCE6-31A6-4087-9206-D20EFC9BD6BC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys Eigenmann &amp; Eigenmann 1889:46" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemipsilichthys Eigenmann and Eigenmann</taxonomicName>
, 1889 currently includes 18 species distributed chiefly in the coastal basins of southern and southeastern Brazil. One species is known from the Amazon. Coastal rivers of southern Brazil, namely the rivers of Santa Catarina State, represent the richest area of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9316BCE6-31A6-4087-9206-D20EFC9BD6BC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys Eigenmann &amp; Eigenmann 1889:46" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemipsilichthys</taxonomicName>
species. The upper Uruguay River in Rio Grande do Sul and Santa Catarina States is inhabited by three species, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:99E338BE-9583-479F-B619-C765DFDC2D99" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys vestigipinnis Pereira &amp; Reis 1992:113" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vestigipinnis">H. vestigipinnis Pereira and Reis</taxonomicName>
, 1992, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E7EF37F0-239F-4981-B469-43D843BC635D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys eurycephalus Pereira &amp; Reis 2002:131" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="eurycephalus">H. eurycephalus Pereira and Reis</taxonomicName>
, 2002, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:47F4AFEB-34AA-4F33-BFA1-DB0E5D924D36" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys hystrix Pereira &amp; Reis 2002:134" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hystrix">H. hystrix Pereira and Reis</taxonomicName>
, 2002. In addition, a small area of endemism composed of the coastal rivers 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Maquiné">Maquine</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Três">Tres</normalizedToken>
Forquilhas, Mampituba and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Araranguá">Ararangua</normalizedToken>
(Reis and Schaefer 1998; Reis and Cardoso 2001), is inhabited by three other species, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7C448DE5-260D-452A-87D4-C5218DA57F23" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys nudulus Reis &amp; Pereira 1999:46" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nudulus">H. nudulus Reis and Pereira</taxonomicName>
, 1999, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:813AB04B-07E1-438B-BC0D-23A19B891561" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys hypselurus Pereira &amp; Reis 2002:136" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hypselurus">H. hypselurus Pereira and Reis</taxonomicName>
, 2002, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E093B3DB-8AFD-4443-A7EF-EACF65C89B6C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys stomias Pereira &amp; Reis 2002:139" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stomias">H. stomias Pereira and Reis</taxonomicName>
, 2002. Finally, remaining coastal rivers of Santa Catarina State north of the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Araranguá">Ararangua</normalizedToken>
River basin are occupied by four additional species, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="calmoni">H. calmoni (Steindachner</taxonomicName>
, 1907), 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:FCB9BEA5-4787-456C-84C4-F2C1FF851950" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys steindachneri Miranda-Ribeiro 1918:107" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="steindachneri">H. steindachneri Miranda Ribeiro</taxonomicName>
, 1918, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F66EA7B4-B6F2-47F4-8CE4-63D44850D1B1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys splendens Bizerril 1995:117" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="splendens">H. splendens Bizerril</taxonomicName>
, 1995, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CE811509-1698-4110-8BEB-E98EA368F5B7" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys azygolechis Pereira &amp; Reis 2002:129" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="azygolechis">H. azygolechis Pereira and Reis</taxonomicName>
, 2002. North of the above area is a geographic gap for 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9316BCE6-31A6-4087-9206-D20EFC9BD6BC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys Eigenmann &amp; Eigenmann 1889:46" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemipsilichthys</taxonomicName>
, and the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Paraíba">Paraiba</normalizedToken>
do Sul River is the next area where species belonging to this genus are found: 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gobio">
H. gobio (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lüt-">Luetken</normalizedToken>
</taxonomicName>
, 1874) and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3E509329-8426-4CFF-98ED-F01FE6B5DBD0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys papillatus Pereira, Oliveira &amp; Oyakawa 2000:378" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="papillatus">H. papillatus Pereira et al.</taxonomicName>
, 2000. Coastal rivers in Rio de Janeiro State, the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Macaé">Macae</normalizedToken>
and Macacu Rivers, are inhabited by 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F8B68095-FB15-48CB-833A-EF2818D575A2" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys garbei Ihering 1911:399" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="garbei">H. garbei Ihering</taxonomicName>
, 1911. Still further north, three species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9316BCE6-31A6-4087-9206-D20EFC9BD6BC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys Eigenmann &amp; Eigenmann 1889:46" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemipsilichthys</taxonomicName>
are found in the upper 
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Francisco River and nearby coastal rivers of Bahia: 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bahianus">H. bahianus (Gosline</taxonomicName>
, 1947), 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9FC5F271-F80A-48BB-B0A2-965E0C06DA83" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys stephanus de Oliveira &amp; Oyakawa 1999:77" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stephanus">H. stephanus Oliveira and Oyakawa</taxonomicName>
, 1999, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:050F358A-27A1-4E2A-AD74-BB6322E2B5B1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys mutuca de Oliveira &amp; Oyakawa 1999:75" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mutuca">H. mutuca Oliveira and Oyakawa</taxonomicName>
, 1999, and in the tributaries of the upper Negro River in the Amazon, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5CC24274-572A-40F3-B283-298AA06DAE46" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys regani Giltay 1936:6" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="regani">H. regani Giltay</taxonomicName>
, 1936. Type locality and distribution of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E16591F3-187A-41C9-ABE1-EFEA74E08AE1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys cerosus Miranda-Ribeiro &amp; Miranda-Ribeiro 1951:xxxix" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cerosus">H. cerosus Miranda Ribeiro</taxonomicName>
, 1951 are not known.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
Pereira and Reis (2002) recently produced a revision of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9316BCE6-31A6-4087-9206-D20EFC9BD6BC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemipsilichthys Eigenmann &amp; Eigenmann 1889:46" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemipsilichthys</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B78878D7-884B-41DA-800B-52C2CBF5B406" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Isbrueckerichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isbrueckerichthys Derijst 1996:64" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isbrueckerichthys Derijst</taxonomicName>
, 1996, describing five new species of the former and redescribing all previously known species. Of the 18 known species, 11 were described during the last ten years and additional undescribed species await formal description. During a survey of coastal rivers on southeastern Brazil one of these undescribed species was detected in the upper 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Perequê-Açu">Pereque-Acu</normalizedToken>
River by the two first authors. Independently, the two last authors also found the same new species during ecological studies in coastal rivers of southeastern Rio de Janeiro State.
</paragraph>
